{{vgname|Wii Sports|官方又称「'''Wii運動'''」}}是一款適用於[[Wii|Wii]][[電子遊戲機|遊樂器]]的[[电子游戏|電子遊戲]]，由[[日本|日本]][[任天堂|任天堂]]公司製作和發行，<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/732/732678p1.html|title=New Wii Titles Announced|publisher=IGN|author=Schneider, Peer|date=2006-09-13|accessdate=2008-02-01|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071126135236/http://wii.ign.com/articles/732/732678p1.html|archive-date=2007-11-26|dead-url=yes}}</ref>屬於[[Wii系列|Wii系列]]的首作和[[Touch!_Generations|Touch! Generations]]系列中的一作。游戏於2006年11月19日在[[北美|北美]]地区随Wii游戏机先行发售，并在随後一个月内於日本、澳大利亚和欧洲发行。2008年，游戏先後在南韩和台湾发行，也成为Wii上为数不多的中文游戏之一。<ref>{{cite web | url = http://wii.cngba.com/wii_xw/2008050935269.shtml | title = 台版Wii发售在即 将捆绑《Wii Sports》中文版 | publisher = 玩家网 | language = zh-cn | date = 2008-05-09 | accessdate = 2009-04-14 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20090210182605/http://wii.cngba.com/wii_xw/2008050935269.shtml | archivedate = 2009-02-10 }}</ref>除日本和韩国外，所有的Wii游戏机均同捆本作销售，<ref name="ign">{{cite web|last=Casamassina|first=Matt|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/745/745708p1.html|publisher=IGN|title=Wii Sports Review|date=2006-11-13|accessdate=2008-01-31|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061115004549/http://wii.ign.com/articles/745/745708p1.html|archive-date=2006-11-15|dead-url=yes}}</ref>使得本作成为自1995年[[Virtual_Boy|Virtual Boy]]平台的《[[马里奥网球|马里奥网球]]》以来，再度綑綁任天堂游戏机販售的首发游戏。

游戏包含了五種[[體育類遊戲|運動模擬遊戲]]，主要是為了向新玩家展示Wii遊樂器的動作感應功能，運動項目包含網球、棒球、保齡球、高爾夫球和拳擊。玩家能使用[[Wii_Remote|Wii手柄]]做出與真實生活中的運動類似之動作，例如揮動網球拍、丟擲保齡球等。<ref name="GamePro">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110417203941/http://www.gamepro.com/article/reviews/86628/wii-sports/|archivedate=2011-04-17|url=http://www.gamepro.com/article/reviews/86628/wii-sports/|title=Review: Wii Sports|date=2006-11-16|publisher=GamePro|accessdate=2008-09-18|language=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>每種運動遊戲的規則都經過簡化，讓剛接觸的玩者容易上手。<ref name="ign" />游戏还拥有练习模式和监测玩家运动进展的体力测定模式。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/GadgetGuide/story?id=2662149|title=Wii Sports -- Wii|publisher=ABC News|date=2006-11-18|accessdate=2008-02-02|language=en|archive-date=2017-12-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171228200922/http://abcnews.go.com/Technology/GadgetGuide/story?id=2662149|dead-url=no}}</ref>

《Wii Sports》获得了媒體的较高评价，并赢得了游戏和娱乐业的多个奖项。游戏含同捆版達到了8,287万套<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/sales/software/wii.html |title=存档副本 |accessdate=2016-11-03 |archive-date=2017-10-14 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171014233725/https://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/sales/software/wii.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>的全球销量，成为史上[[最畅销电子游戏列表|第四畅销的电子游戏]]，仅次于《[[我的世界|-{zh-cn:我的世界;zh-tw:當個創世神;zh-hk:當個創世神;}-]]》、《[[俄罗斯方块|俄罗斯方块]]》和《[[俠盜獵車手V|俠盜獵車手V]]》，同时也是單一遊戲主機平台上最为畅销的电子游戏。<ref name="081031e">{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2009/090130e.pdf#page=6|title=Financial Results Briefing for the Six-Month Period Ended December 2008|publisher=任天堂|date=2008-10-31|format=[[PDF|PDF]]|accessdate=2009-01-30|pages=6|language=en|archive-date=2011-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110430043326/http://www.nintendo.co.jp/ir/pdf/2009/090130e.pdf#page=6|dead-url=no}}</ref>现在，《Wii Sports》已成为电视商业广告、新闻报道和其他节目中Wii的象徵性代表，<ref name="WiiCommercial">{{cite web |url=http://media.wii.ign.com/articles/746/746137/vids_1.html |title=Official Wii commercial |work=[[IGN|IGN]] |publisher=任天堂 |date=2006-11-14 |accessdate=2008-02-02 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070302222406/http://media.wii.ign.com/articles/746/746137/vids_1.html |archivedate=2007-03-02 }}</ref><ref name="ABC-Video1">{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Video/playerIndex?id=3313748&affil=ktrk|title=Nintendo Adds an 'I' to Wiimbledon|publisher=ABC News|date=2007-06-25|accessdate=2008-02-02|language=en|archive-date=2016-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307023954/http://abcnews.go.com/Video/playerIndex?id=3313748&affil=ktrk|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Conan">{{cite web|url=http://www.joystiq.com/2007/02/02/conan-takes-on-serena-in-wii-tennis/|title=Conan takes on Serena in Wii Tennis|last=Miller|first=Ross|publisher=Joystiq|date=2007-02-02|accessdate=2008-02-01|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090130021259/http://www.joystiq.com/2007/02/02/conan-takes-on-serena-in-wii-tennis/|archive-date=2009-01-30|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref name="Mercer">{{cite web|url=http://www.n-sider.com/contentview.php?contentid=3531|title=Chrétien delivers Wii knock-out punch|last=Bergmann|first=Dean|publisher=N-Sider|date=2007-02-02|accessdate=2008-09-18|language=en|archive-date=2017-08-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170814140518/http://www.n-sider.com/contentview.php?contentid=3531}}</ref>更成为各年龄层玩家聚会和竞赛的流行方式。<ref name="ABC-Video1" /><ref name="Seniors">{{cite web |url=http://marketplace.publicradio.org/display/web/2007/12/11/old_wii/ |title=Seniors becoming old hands at Wii |publisher=American Public Media |work=Marketplace |last=Collins |first=Jennifer |date=2007-12-11 |accessdate=2008-01-31 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080512184045/http://marketplace.publicradio.org/display/web/2007/12/11/old_wii/ |archivedate=2008-05-12 }}</ref><ref name="TennisTourn">{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/755/755020p1.html|title=Wii Tennis Tourney in Melbourne|last=Kolan|first=Patrick|date=2007-01-11|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2008-02-01|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070622091729/http://wii.ign.com/articles/755/755020p1.html|archive-date=2007-06-22|dead-url=yes}}</ref>遊戲續作是《[[Wii運動_度假勝地|度假勝地]]》、《[[Wii_Sports_Club|俱樂部]]》及《[[Nintendo_Switch_運動|Nintendo Switch 運動]]》。

== 游戏要素 ==

[[File:WS-WiiRemote_Example.jpg|thumb]]游戏中使用[[Wii_Remote|Wii 手柄]]模仿挥杆动作]]
《Wii Sports》的主菜单中提供有五種独立的運動項目：[[网球|网球]]、[[棒球|棒球]]、[[保龄球|保龄球]]、[[高爾夫球|高尔夫球]]和[[拳击|拳击]]。<ref name="ign" /><ref name="GameTrailers">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090429053615/http://www.gametrailers.com/player/15056.html?type=flv|archivedate=2009-04-29|url=http://www.gametrailers.com/player/15056.html?type=flv|title=Wii Sports Review|publisher=GameTrailers|date=2006-11-15|accessdate=2007-05-01|language=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>游戏使用Wii左右手柄的运动传感器功能控制屏幕中角色的动作，使玩家能以类似於生活中各项目真实的运动方式移动手柄，例如，可以像拿[[高爾夫球桿|高爾夫球桿]]、[[球棒|球棒]]或[[保龄球|保龄球]]一样握住和挥动手柄。<ref name="GamePro" />游戏部分操作交由[[人工智能|电脑]]控制：在网球中，Wii会自动控制玩家的移动，玩家只需负责挥[[球拍|球拍]]；棒球游戏则需要[[击球员|击球]]和[[投手|投球]]，所有的防守均由Wii处理；在拳擊比賽中，玩家可揮拳攻擊或閃躲，且可使出[[鉤拳|鉤拳]]、反擊拳等高階技巧。<ref name="GameTrailers" />

每个游戏项都拥有标准游戏模式、练习模式和多人模式。<ref name="ign" />标准游戏模式依照各项目的规则进行：双打制网球、棒球击球和投球、十瓶十格制保龄球、3洞或9洞高尔夫球和三局制拳击。<ref name="Instructions">{{cite book|year=2006|title= Wii Sports Instruction Booklet|publisher=任天堂|language = en}}</ref>练习模式为单人游戏，可供玩家练习各项目的特定技巧，并可以获得[[奖牌|奖牌]]奖励。<ref name="GameTrailers" /><ref name="WiiHandbook08">{{citation| title = Wii Sports Training| issue = Winter Special 2008| periodical = Nintendo Power| publisher = Future Publishing| date = 2008| pages = 28–35|language = en}}</ref>每个项目均设有单人和双人游戏模式，有些还允许最多4名玩家参与。<ref name="Instructions" />保龄球和高尔夫球可让多名玩家轮流使用一只Wii手柄，<ref name="GameTrailers" />而网球则要求玩家人手一只。《Wii Sports》的多人模式通常会让玩家在运动中相互竞争，网球则是唯一的例外，可以允许两名玩家选择同场协作或是对抗。<ref name="WiiHandbook08" />

游戏角色均取自Wii的[[Wii_Channels#Mii频道|Mii频道]]，该频道可让用户创建可用於游戏的专属“Mii”（即自定义[[纸娃娃系统|虚拟角色]]）。《Wii Sports》也是Wii上最先使用这一功能的游戏，<ref name="ign" />保存在Wii上的Mii会出现在保龄球赛的人群在和玩家控制的棒球队中，而[[非玩家角色|非玩家角色（NPC）]]也同样由Mii频道工具创建。在一台Wii上建立的Mii可以传输到Wii手柄的記憶體中，方便在另一台Wii上使用。<ref name="Instructions" />

=== 游戏进程 ===

游戏之後，根据玩家的表现，系统会给予其技能点的奖励或惩罚，但在多人模式中则不进行记分。游戏会以图表的形式跟踪玩家得分，玩家在得到1000技能点後即可获得“高手”级评价，以及其Mii的化妆功能，同时会在[[Wii_Channels#留言板|Wii留言板]]收到相应的通知消息。在拳击和网球的单人游戏中，观众的规模会随球员的技术水平增长。通过赢得足够场次的游戏比赛，Mii的技能等级最高可达2399，之後便无法继续提高。产生这一问题是由於玩家等级过高，导致显示技能等级的图表超出屏幕之外所致。《Wii Sports》还具有测算玩家体力年龄的功能，该测试会从练习模式随机选择三项挑战，并对玩家的表现加以评定，根据玩家的实际年龄、平衡、速度和耐力等因素计算出其体力年龄。每个Mii每天只能测试一次，体力年龄的测定结果会以图表的形式每一个、两个或三个月刊登在Wii留言板上。<ref name="Instructions" /><ref name="WiiHandbook08" />

== 开发 ==

[[File:Iwata-e3-2006_crop.jpg|thumb]]在[[任天堂|任天堂]]的2006年[[E3电子娱乐展|E3]]发表会上]]
《Wii Sports》由[[任天堂情报开发本部|任天堂情报开发本部]]的软件开发二组主管[[江口胜也|江口胜也]]出品。<ref name="EguchiInterview">{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/709/709218p1.html|title=Interview: Wii Sports|last=Casamassina|first=Matt|date=2006-05-18|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2008-02-01|language=en|archive-date=2006-08-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060809043119/http://wii.ign.com/articles/709/709218p1.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>随着Wii的发售，任天堂希望吸引更多从未接触过电子游戏的人们，为此，他们需要多款能让新老玩家都可共享乐趣的游戏产品。<ref name="Conference">{{cite web |url=http://e3.gamespot.com/2006/story.html?sid=6149663 |title=E3 06: Wii unveiled at Nintendo's E3 conference |last=Surette |first=Tim |coauthors=Dan Tochen |publisher=GameSpot |date=2006-05-09 |accessdate=2008-02-09 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807084122/http://e3.gamespot.com/2006/story.html?sid=6149663 |archivedate=2011-08-07 }}</ref>此外，任天堂还希望玩家能每天使用Wii。为了实现这一目标，《Wii Sports》被有意地打造为了Wii的旗舰产品。<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.joystiq.com/2006/06/19/miyamoto-wii-sports-will-be-flagship-title-wiimote-not-finaliz/| title = Miyamoto: Wii Sports will be flagship title, Wiimote not finalized| publisher = Joystiq| first = James| last = Ransom-Wiley| date = 2006-06-19| accessdate = 2008-02-09| language = en| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090925060635/http://www.joystiq.com/2006/06/19/miyamoto-wii-sports-will-be-flagship-title-wiimote-not-finaliz| archive-date = 2009-09-25| dead-url = yes}}</ref>作为一个简单的引导性作品，《Wii Sports》的设计初衷就是要同时让玩家和非玩家乐在其中，<ref name="WalkLine">{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/717/717268p1.html|title=Wii Sports: Walking the Line|last=Bozon|first=Mark|publisher=IGN|date=2006-07-07|accessdate=2008-02-05|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080302042933/http://wii.ign.com/articles/717/717268p1.html|archive-date=2008-03-02|dead-url=yes}}</ref>因而大众喜闻乐见的体育便获选为主题。游戏的设计思想在於简单易上手，人人可玩，而不是专业的运动模拟或是逼真的画面。为了保持简单的特性，诸如网球中的跑动等操作均被取消。<ref name="EguchiInterview" />在开发过程中，[[马力欧|马里奥]]系列角色曾出现在游戏，但由於玩家的反馈更偏爱於Mii而遭到尽数移除。<ref name="GDC07">{{cite web |url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/6167078.html |title=GDC 07: Miyamoto speaks |first=Brendan |last=Sinclair |publisher=GameSpot |date=2007-03-08 |accessdate=2008-03-13 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070321091455/http://www.gamespot.com/news/6167078.html |archivedate=2007-03-21 }}</ref>游戏支持[[纵横比_(图像)|16:9宽屏显示]]和[[逐行扫描|逐行扫描]]，以每秒60[[帧率|帧]]运行，<ref name="ign" />并利用Wii遥控器的[[加速规|加速规]]测量玩家的运动。<ref name="10min">{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/706/706071p1.html|title=E3 2006: 10 Minutes with Nintendo Tennis|last=Casamassina|first=Matt|date=2006-05-09|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2008-02-05|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071114220607/http://wii.ign.com/articles/706/706071p1.html|archive-date=2007-11-14|dead-url=yes}}</ref>为了儘可能地贴近现实，投球和击球等运动感应功能成为了游戏的首要考虑因素。<ref name="GDC07" />《Wii Sports》之所以与Wii同捆销售，是因为任天堂并没有期望玩家单单为了这一游戏而去买游戏机。任天堂认为通过随机附带，玩家会有更大可能玩到这款游戏，而一旦他们喜欢上了的话，这份乐趣便会蔓延开来。<ref name="QA-Iwata">{{cite web|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120119154817/http://www.gamespot.com/news/6185358.html|archivedate=2012-01-19|url=http://www.gamespot.com/news/6185358.html|title=Q&A: Nintendo's Satoru Iwata|last=Ogawa|first=Yohei|coauthors=Randolph Ramsay, Tor Thorsen|publisher=GameSpot|date=2008-02-05|accessdate=2008-02-05|language=en|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在2006年的[[E3电子娱乐展|E3媒体与商业峰会]]游戏展之前，《Wii Sports：网球》成为游戏公开的第一项运动，并在任天堂的E3展前发表会上公布为一款运动游戏合集中的一部分。<ref name="10min" />社长[[岩田聪|岩田聪]]以“Wii Sports”之名介绍了这款合集，并透露其中包含有网球、高尔夫球和棒球。现场展出了游戏视频和台上实机演示，在网球双打演示中，岩田聪和美国任天堂总裁雷吉同组与[[宮本茂|宫本茂]]和一名网络竞赛赢家斯科特·代尔组成的另一组现场较量。<ref name="Conference" />其餘的体育游戏也在E3上以相似的命名方式一一展出，包括《Wii Sports：棒球》、《Wii Sports：高尔夫》和《Wii Sports：飞机》。<ref name="SportsPack">{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/707/707417p1.html|title=E3 2006: Hands-On: Wii Sports Pack|publisher=IGN|last=Iverson|first=Dan|date=2006-05-10|accessdate=2008-02-05|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071216045759/http://wii.ign.com/articles/707/707417p1.html|archive-date=2007-12-16|dead-url=yes}}</ref>当时，棒球游戏仅能模拟击球动作，<ref>{{cite web |url=http://e3.gamespot.com/2006/story.html?sid=6150628 |title=E3 06: Wii Sports: Baseball Hands-On |last=Ekberg |first=Brian |publisher=GameSpot |date=2006-05-10 |accessdate=2008-02-06 |language=en |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110807084127/http://e3.gamespot.com/2006/story.html?sid=6150628 |archivedate=2011-08-07 }}</ref>而飞机游戏则类似於《[[飛行俱樂部|飞行俱乐部]]》，要求玩家在时限内驾驶飞机通-{}-过一个个吊环。<ref name="SportsPack" />游戏最终并没有收录这一项目，但一般相信它会出现在未来名为“Wii Motor Sports”的游戏中。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/objects/826/826991.html|title=Wii Motor Sports Airplane|publisher=IGN|accessdate=2008-02-08|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090125010909/http://wii.ign.com/objects/826/826991.html|archive-date=2009-01-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref>在2006年9月14日的美国新闻发布会上，雷吉宣布《Wii Sports》将随Wii免费附赠，保龄球和拳击游戏也会包含其中。<ref name="IGN-Bowling">{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/745/745356p1.html|title=Hands-on: Wii Sports|publisher=IGN|last=Harris|first=Craig|date=2006-11-10|accessdate=2007-05-01|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070621203915/http://wii.ign.com/articles/745/745356p1.html|archive-date=2007-06-21|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

== 评价 ==

《Wii Sports》在商业上获得了空前成功，截止到2007年便成为最为畅销的Wii游戏。<ref name="GWR08">{{cite book |editor=Craig Glenday|title=Guinness World Records Gamer's Edition 2008|url=https://archive.org/details/guinnessworldrec00guin_0|series=Guinness World Records|date=2008-03-11| publisher=Guinnes|isbn= 978-1-904994-21-3|chapter=Hardware: Best-Sellers by Platform|page=[https://archive.org/details/guinnessworldrec00guin_0/page/50 50]|language = en}}</ref>在并未随机同捆销售的日本，游戏发行两天内即售出了176,167套，创下[[电子游戏机#歷史|第七世代游戏机]]游戏在日销售纪录。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://wii.ign.com/articles/749/749151p1.html|title=Wii Sports No. 1 in Japan|publisher=IGN|last=Gantayat|first=Anoop|date=2006-12-04|accessdate=2008-01-31|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071016213256/http://wii.ign.com/articles/749/749151p1.html|archive-date=2007-10-16|dead-url=yes}}</ref>截至2007年2月，游戏已售出100万餘份。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.joystiq.com/2007/03/20/wii-play-joins-sports-with-platinum-sales-in-japan/|title=Wii Play joins Sports with platinum sales in Japan|last=Miller|first=Ross|publisher=Joystiq|date=2007-03-20|accessdate=2008-02-08|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090508190227/http://www.joystiq.com/2007/03/20/wii-play-joins-sports-with-platinum-sales-in-japan/|archive-date=2009-05-08|dead-url=yes}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.joystiq.com/2007/02/15/japanese-software-sales-week-ending-02-11-07/|title=Japanese software sales: week ending 02.11.07|last=Davies|first=Jonti|publisher=Joystiq|date=2007-02-15|accessdate=2008-02-08|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090403003946/http://www.joystiq.com/2007/02/15/japanese-software-sales-week-ending-02-11-07/|archive-date=2009-04-03|dead-url=yes}}</ref>游戏业调查公司Media Create亦在同年五月初将《Wii Sports》评为日本游戏20强排名中的第三位。<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.gamespot.com/wii/sports/wiisports/news.html?sid=6170684|title=Top 21 Japanese games all Nintendo|publisher=GameSpot|date=2007-05-12|accessdate=2008-02-06|language = en}}</ref>游戏以1,911,520的销量荣登2007年度日本畅销游戏榜首，<ref name="Gamasutra">{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=16914|title=Wii Sports Named Best Selling Game Of 2007 In Japan|publisher=Gamasutra|last=Jenkins|first=David|date=2008-01-11|accessdate=2008-01-31|language=en|archive-date=2008-02-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080218025727/http://www.gamasutra.com/php-bin/news_index.php?story=16914|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.mcvuk.com/news/29249/SPECIAL-REPORT-Japans-2007-market-stats-in-full | title=Special Report: Japan’s 2007 market stats in full | accessdate=2008-02-02 | author=Neil Long | date=2008-01-07 | work=Market for Home Computing and Video Games | publisher=Intent Media | language=en | archive-date=2008-02-10 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080210000232/http://www.mcvuk.com/news/29249/SPECIAL-REPORT-Japans-2007-market-stats-in-full | dead-url=no }}</ref>并在2008年以841,736套的成绩蝉联销量第一。<ref name="famitsu2008">{{cite web|title=Japanese 2008 Market Report|url=http://www.mcvuk.com/features/403/JAPANESE-2008-MARKET-REPORT|publisher=MCVUK|accessdate=2009-01-09|language=en|archive-date=2009-04-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090402121525/http://www.mcvuk.com/features/403/JAPANESE-2008-MARKET-REPORT|dead-url=no}}</ref>据任天堂统计，截止到2008年12月31日，游戏已经在全球售出4050万套（含同捆版）。<ref name="081031e" /><!-- ''[[Famitsu|Famitsu]]'' reported that by the end of June 2008, it has sold 3,009,692 copies in [[Japan|Japan]].<ref>Weekly Famitsu, issue 1020</ref> -->

=== 媒体评论 ===

